ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: WHOLESALE MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF FOR SALES OF CAPACITY, ENERGY, ANCILLARY SERVICES

record_data.record_plain_text: AES OHIO GENERATION, LLC WHOLESALE MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF PROVIDING FOR SALES OF CAPACITY, ENERGY AND ANCILLARY SERVICES I. General Purpose. The purpose of this Rate Schedule is for AES Ohio Generation, LLC (the Company or Seller ) to: (a) sell to unaffiliated purchasers electric capacity, energy and ancillary services at market-based rates; (b) broker at no charge to or from The Dayton Power and Light Company ( DP&L ), capacity, energy and ancillary services subject to the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission s (the Commission ) standards regarding the brokering of affiliated utility capacity and energy; and (c) to engage in other related marketing and brokering activities permitted by the Commission. This Rate Schedule shall become effective on the date established by the Commission. II. Definitions The following words and terms used herein shall be understood to have the following meanings: 1. Affiliate: In the case of any exempt wholesale generator defined under Section 32(a) of the Public Utility Holding Company Act of 1935, as amended, affiliate is defined in accordance with Section 214 of the Federal Power Act. In the case of any other entity, affiliate is defined in accordance with 18 C.F.R. 161.2(a). 2. Buyer means a purchaser of electric capacity, energy and/or ancillary services or resold transmission rights under this Tariff. 3. Commission means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or such successor Federal regulatory agency as may have jurisdiction over this Tariff. 4. Mitigated Balancing Authority Area means the area within which PJM Interconnection, LLC has operational control of transmission facilities. 5. PJM means the PJM Interconnection, LLC or any successor thereto. 6. Seller means AES Ohio Generation, LLC. 7. Tariff means this wholesale market-based rate tariff, as amended from time to time. 8. Service Agreement means an agreement entered into by Seller and Buyer for service under this Tariff as it may be amended from time to time. III. Availability. This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric capacity, energy and ancillary services to the extent authorized by the Commission and not otherwise subject to another tariff that is in effect. IV. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. V. Ancillary services. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which include spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM, and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchases for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. VI. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission s regulations, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16, and Parts 41, 101, and 141; and received blanket approval under Part 34. DPL Energy, Inc., et al., 76 FERC 61,367 (1996). VII. Rates, Terms and Conditions. All sales pursuant to this Tariff shall be made at rates established by and subject to the terms and conditions of a service agreement between Buyer and Seller. VIII. Seller Category. Seller meets the criteria for being a Category 1 seller in the Northwest, Southeast, and Southwest Power Pool regions and a Category 2 seller in the Northeast, Southwest and Central Regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
